Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 14 MRSA ยง6030-K is enacted to read:
3 ยง6030-K. Model residential lease
4 1. Model residential lease. By December 1, 2025, the Attorney General shall create
5 and post on its publicly accessible website a model lease for residential property that
6 complies with current law, including any disclosure and any document required to be
7 attached to a residential lease. The Attorney General shall update the model lease
8 biennially and post the revised model lease no later than December 1st of every odd-
9 numbered year. In creating and revising a model lease under this subsection, the Attorney
10 General shall consult with one or more tenant advocacy organizations and one or more
11 landlord advocacy organizations.
12 2. Neutrality. A model lease under subsection 1 may not favor the rights and interests
13 of either a tenant or a landlord.
14 3. Public comment. The Attorney General shall post for public comment a draft of
15 the model lease on a publicly accessible website for 30 days prior to posting the model
16 lease under subsection 1.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This bill requires the Attorney General to create and post on its publicly accessible
1199 website a model residential lease that complies with current law, including any disclosure
2200 and any document required to be attached to a residential lease, and to update the model
2211 lease biennially. The bill requires the Attorney General to consult with one or more tenant
2222 advocacy organizations and one or more landlord advocacy organizations in creating and
2233 revising the model lease. It requires that the model lease be neutral and not favor either
2244 tenant or landlord rights and interests and requires posting for public comment a draft of
2255 the model lease on a publicly accessible website for 30 days prior to posting the final
2266 version.
